{"timestamp": "2026-06-12T12:33:29.493391", "query": "what is aws and why it is used?", "response": "**1. Direct Answer**\n\nAWS (Amazon Web Services) is a segment of Amazon that consists of amounts earned from global sales of compute, storage, database, and other services for start-ups, enterprises, government agencies, and academic institutions. It offers a broad set of on-demand technology services, including compute, storage, database, analytics, artificial intelligence, and machine learning, and other services to developers.\n\n**2. Supporting Evidence**\n\n- \"The AWS segment consists of amounts earned from global sales of compute, storage, database, and other services for start-ups, enterprises, government agencies, and academic institutions.\" (Source: Amazon-2025-annual-report.pdf, page 25)\n- \"We serve developers and enterprises of all sizes, including start-ups, government agencies, and academic institutions, through AWS, which offers a broad set of on-demand technology services, including compute, storage, database, analytics, artificial intelligence and machine learning, and other services.\" (Source: Amazon-2025-annual-report.pdf, page (not specified))\n- \"To best take advantage of these continued advances in technology, we are investing in AWS, which offers a broad set of on-demand technology services, including compute, storage, database, analytics, and machine learning, and other services to developers\" (Source: Amazon-2025-annual-report.pdf, page (not specified))\n\n**3. Sources**\n\n- \"Amazon-2025-annual-report.pdf\"\n\n**4. Confidence**\n\n- High: The answer is directly stated in the provided document, and multiple evidence sources support the claim.", "sources": "data/raw/Amazon-2025-Annual-Report.pdf"}
{"timestamp": "2026-06-12T12:34:43.220954", "query": "list down there  Rapidly Evolving Business Model ", "response": "**1. Direct Answer**\n\nOur rapidly evolving business model is characterized by the following:\n\n- Rapid expansion into new products, services, technologies, and geographic regions\n- Highly competitive and rapidly changing industry landscape\n- Dependence on continued growth of demand for our products and services\n- Volatility in stock price due to various market and economic factors\n\n**2. Supporting Evidence**\n\n- \"Our Expansion into New Products, Services, Technologies, and Geographic Regions Subjects Us to Additional Risks\" (Source: Amazon-2025-annual-report.pdf, page 6)\n- \"We have a rapidly evolving business model.\" (Source: Amazon-2025-annual-report.pdf, page 14)\n- \"We have organized our operations into three segments: North America, International, and AWS. These segments reflect the way the Company evaluates its business performance and manages its operations.\" (Source: Amazon-2025-annual-report.pdf, page (not specified))\n- \"Our business is affected by, among other things, general economic, business, and geopolitical conditions worldwide.\" (Source: Amazon-2025-annual-report.pdf, page 14)\n- \"Our revenue growth may not be sustainable, and our percentage growth rates may decrease.\" (Source: Amazon-2025-annual-report.pdf, page 14)\n- \"We face intense competition\" (Source: Amazon-2025-annual-report.pdf, page 6)\n\n**3. Sources**\n\n- \"Amazon-2025-annual-report.pdf\"", "sources": "data/raw/Amazon-2025-Annual-Report.pdf"}
